Feedback/question, regarding the MARF Merkle proof.

At this point, the proof verification process helps asserting that “a given key exists at this particular block”, but does not help checking the value of the key. 
The proof constructor does this job here: 
https://github.com/blockstack/blockstack-core/blob/f2322c2fffb8c0b01c0ecfa07192870facb7a743/src/chainstate/stacks/index/proofs.rs#L1088-L1091
However Merkle proofs are meant to be manipulated off-chain (at least in my mind 🙂), and no one can have the guaranty that a given proof have been build with this function.
This nuance is surely irrelevant in the cases of transactions, since we will probably use the transaction hash as a key. Knowing that “a given key exists at this particular block” will naturally be implying that the transaction is part of this block.

However, when something else than the value’s hash is used as a key, the construct might look incomplete, because the proof just informs you that a given key exists, without telling you much about its value. 
That could maybe be fine in a world where double insertions would be rejected but since we’re updating the values, isn’t it an issue?

```rust
    #[test]
    fn toying_with_proofs() {
        let path = "/tmp/toying_with_marf".to_string();
        match fs::metadata(&path) {
            Ok(_) => {
                fs::remove_dir_all(&path).unwrap();
            },
            Err(_) => {}
        };

        let mut m = MARF::from_path(&path).unwrap();

        let sentinel_block = TrieFileStorage::block_sentinel();
        let block_0 = BlockHeaderHash([0u8; 32]);
        let block_1 = BlockHeaderHash([1u8; 32]);
        let block_2 = BlockHeaderHash([2u8; 32]);

        let k1 = "K1".to_string();
        let old_v = "OLD".to_string();
        let new_v = "NEW".to_string();

        m.begin(&sentinel_block, &block_0).unwrap();
        m.commit().unwrap();

        // Block #1
        m.begin(&block_0, &block_1).unwrap();
        let r = m.insert(&k1, &old_v);
        m.commit();

        // Block #2
        m.begin(&block_1, &block_2).unwrap();
        let r = m.insert(&k1, &new_v);
        m.commit();

        let old_value = m.get(&block_1, &k1);
        println!("OLD: {:?}", old_value);

        let new_value = m.get(&block_2, &k1).unwrap().unwrap();
        println!("NEW: {:?}", new_value);
        
        let path = TriePath::from_key(&k1);

        // Pass :)
        merkle_test_marf_key_value(&mut m.storage, &block_2, &k1, &new_v);

        // Pass :( after commenting proofs.rs:1090
        merkle_test_marf_key_value(&mut m.storage, &block_2, &k1, &old_v);
    }
```

